𝐃𝐚𝐲 𝟐𝟒 – 𝐋𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧 𝐆𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧 𝐀𝟏 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐌𝐞: 𝐌𝐲 𝐅𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐆𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐧! 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦



After mastering how to say "mine" and "yours," let's put it to use by talking about something very important: family! Knowing how to introduce your family members is a lovely step in connecting with others in German.



👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 "𝐃𝐢𝐞 𝐅𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐞" - 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐅𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐲

The German word for family is die Familie (feminine noun).

To say "My family is big/small," you can say:

- Meine Familie ist groß. (My family is big.)

- Meine Familie ist klein. (My family is small.)



🌳 The Family Tree: "Der Stammbaum" or "Der Familienbaum"

Here are some key family members in German. Notice how we use "mein" and "meine" based on their gender!

der Großvater (grandfather) – mein Großvater

die Großmutter (grandmother) – meine Großmutter

der Vater (father) – mein Vater

die Mutter (mother) – meine Mutter

der Bruder (brother) – mein Bruder

die Schwester (sister) – meine Schwester

der Onkel (uncle) – mein Onkel

die Tante (aunt) – meine Tante

der Cousin (male cousin) – mein Cousin

die Cousine (female cousin) – meine Cousine

ich (I / me) – This is where "you" are in the family tree!



🗣️ Examples in Sentences:

- Das ist meine Mutter. (This is my mother.) 

- Das ist mein Onkel. (This is my uncle.) 

- Ich habe einen Bruder und eine Schwester. (I have a brother and a sister.)

- Meine Großeltern leben in Berlin. (My grandparents live in Berlin.)

- Hast du Geschwister? (Do you have siblings?)

- Ja, ich habe zwei Schwestern. (Yes, I have two sisters.)

Nein, ich habe keine Geschwister. (No, I don't have any siblings.)



✍️ Practice Tip:

Try to draw your own family tree and label everyone in German! Introduce a few family members to yourself in German, like "Das ist mein Vater" or "Das ist meine Schwester."



